What you need to know:  Coe said that the involvement of government departments like the medical, immigration, judiciary, Directorate of Criminal Investigation (DCI), the Office of the Director of Public Prosecutions (ODPP), Athletics Kenya and Anti-Doping Agency of Kenya (ADAK) will be key in the successful fight against the viceCoe explained that the meeting with President William Ruto and Cabinet Secretary for Sports Ababu Namwamba gave him enough time to understand the commitment across government departmentsCoe said working to resolve the high number of positive tests on road running will hopefully set the stage to move Kenya out of Category “A”